Hey

Merging of PR: https://github.com/alecthomas/voluptuous/pull/311 has resulted in tests failure in the master branch. 

@dtao: Please look into this.

```python
all_statements_copy = list(all_statements)
for statement in all_statements_copy:
    response_exists = False
    for s in all_statements_copy:
        if statement in s.in_response_to:
            response_exists = True
            break # Exit for loop since one exists

    if not response_exists:
        all_statements.remove(statement)
```
Pretty sure this is very inefficient when dealing with larger datasets

changing to this does what the comment says (and is much faster):

```python
responses = set()
to_remove = list()
for statement in all_statements:
    for response in statement.in_response_to:
        responses.add(response[0])
for statement in all_statements:
    if statement.text not in responses:
        to_remove.append(statement)

for statement in to_remove:
    all_statements.remove(statement)
```

