@xlvector @antinucleon: currently, there is no clean way to feed tensors of shape `[sequence, batch, feature size]` into WarpCTC: it only takes `[sequence x batch, feature size]`, and there is no nice syntax with Reshape to produce this form from `[sequence, batch, feature size]` (Reshape layer doesn't have a nice way of doing this. You need to explicitly state the sequence + batch size, which makes executor reshaping ugly). 

`[sequence x batch, feature size]` is also very confusing to people, as they don't know what order batch and sequence appear in for the underlying data. In addition, they need to specify the sequence length ("input_length") and label length explicitly, which would just be inferred from the input tensor if you used  `[sequence, batch, feature size]`.

So: should we change `[sequence x batch, feature size]` to  `[sequence, batch, feature size]` and break backward compatibility, or just add support for Rank-3 inputs that will be interpreted as  `[sequence, batch, feature size]`?

